node.text: A quick ride off the shores of Miami is beautiful Bimini, an island I hold close to my heart. Filmed this three years ago & finally brought it to life. Leave your feedback in the comments! 🤙 This mystic, gorgeous & historical island has been loved by everyone from Ernest Hemingway to Martin Luther King Jr. For those who love tropical vibes, adventure, & culture - this island must go on your bucketlist! 🐬 Id love your support! Don’t forget to share this video, tag friends & like this post. Love you Grubfam! 🙏 Thanks for the assist on filming @znicolaou & as always, thank you for making my vision come to life, @jessyfiggsfilmsphotography ❗️ #TheGrubfather #Bimini #Bahamas #BiminiBliss

❗️THE BEST & EASIEST TUNA SALAD RECIPE 🐟 Tbh, I was never a huge fan of tuna salad until I created this recipe which is a wild flavor ride. I’ve got the full recipe listed below and trust me: You won’t be able to eat it any other way after you try this. ✔️ Please note: The key here is HIGH QUALITY TUNA - low in mercury and preferably wild caught. 👌 

👇 GRUB TUNA SALAD 👇 
1️⃣ Open three cans of tuna, put in a big mixing bowl. 
2️⃣ Cover with four heavy teaspoons of mayonnaise, two heavy teaspoons of Dijon mustard. 
3️⃣ Drizzle in sriracha, mustard powder, garlic powder and cayenne to taste. Roughly half a teaspoon - teaspoon of each. 
4️⃣ I also use @HighNoteHotSauce’s green sauce - it’s not necessary but if you can, it kicks it up a level. 
5️⃣ Beat tuna and add ins heavy until well blended. Layer in olive oil, salt and pepper to taste. 
6️⃣ Line potato hot dog buns with bib or butter lettuce, layer in tuna fish salad. 
7️⃣ Sprinkle with red onion + scallion on top. 
8️⃣ EAT THE DANG THING! 😋 

💯 Trust me when I say this will be your new go to tuna salad recipe! Feel free to add tweaks that fit your style.

👀 Love food? Love recipes? Love travel? Hit me with a follow if it’s your first time here: @THEGRUBFATHER ✌️ Much love! #TheGrubfather #Recipes

👉 This bakery is super unique as it draws its recipes + inspiration from the owner’s Sicilian + Korean roots. That means you’re getting two styles of baking in all of their food. Fusion that works is always dreamy. 👌 

👀 Go check out my stories today to see more and stay tuned for my reel later tonight if you love donuts. Their version of Italian bombolones is… beautiful. 😏

❗️CHEESY STEAK PINWHEEL BURGER HACK 👉 Take your BBQ game up a notch by combining two classics: PINWHEELS + BURGERS 🔥 I’m always looking for ways to amp up things I love and this simple lil technique is a home-run. 

✔️ The combos you can do with this are endless but I took a steak, spinach & mozz pinwheel & stuffed it into buns I turned into garlic bread. Add some roasted red peps and bada bing, bada boom - you got something real tasty in ya hands. 😋

💪 2020 vs 2021 👉 180 vs 150! My fitness journey has been a complicated one as my relationship with food, as you all know, is an interesting one. I debated posting this because it’s not something I’m too open about… But I want to change that! ✔️ I can’t tell you how many times I get asked “how do you stay so small with all this food?!” and the fact is that it wasn’t always that way and it definitely comes down to a few things: 

1️⃣ Intermittent fasting! This is a MAJOR 🔑 

2️⃣ Eliminating sugar intake when I’m not shooting / taste testing - sometimes dipping into ketosis.

3️⃣ Putting in *meaningful* work at the gym, which my trainer @RVTFITNESS has been such a huge help with. 

4️⃣ Allowing myself to enjoy the foods I love, but doing so in moderation and with gratitude. 

5️⃣ When you want to give up, go deeper into it. Develop a beast mode mentality and hold yourself to the highest standard! 

❗️This page is undeniably a vessel of indulgent, GRUB-centric food. That will never change. But I think my duty as a public figure in the food space is to also provide some health conscious recipes, restaurant dishes + tips as well. So expect some of that in the coming weeks. 

💥 These past few months I’ve learned that health is such a beautiful achievement. Health doesn’t mean skinny either, it means feeling good at your core in both body + mind. ♥️ 

🏃‍♂️ As I’ve always said, The Grubfam aka YOU is like my family. We’ve built such a beautiful platform together. If I can provide even a spark of inspiration for you to embark on a fitness / health journey (while also giving you allll the cheat day recommendations) that would make my heart and spirit full. 

👀 Let me know what you think!

Much love,
Sal ✌️ #TheGrubfather
